the current opioid drug
epidemic.

35:45.510 --> 35:48.313 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SAUER, Kentucky: People
get hooked
on it and can't get off of it,
or don't want

35:48.346 --> 35:52.550 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to, causing a lot of younger
generation to
lose their lives.

35:52.584 --> 35:57.255 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And by younger
generation, Sauer
means his middle-aged neighbors,
who, as we

35:57.288 --> 36:03.328 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
